WEBVTT

00:03.522 --> 00:04.764
Welcome to Gospel and Life.

00:05.525 --> 00:09.510
How can you become the kind of person whose character deepens during hardship?

00:10.231 --> 00:14.637
The Apostle Peter tells us it's a supernatural work of God that reshapes the heart.

00:15.138 --> 00:23.029
Today, Tim Keller shows us how only a reborn, renewed heart can love others well and face suffering with hope, courage, and joy.

00:23.049 --> 00:32.722
Tonight we celebrate the Lord's Supper.

00:32.834 --> 00:43.211
But we try to concentrate our teaching time, try to make a little bit shorter, and also try to focus on just one subject, one idea.

00:43.231 --> 00:45.434
I love the Lord's Supper evenings.

00:45.975 --> 00:48.399
I only do it once a month.

00:49.000 --> 00:55.510
What I like about it, of course, is I like to have time to process the truth.

00:56.732 --> 00:59.036
I like to be able to take the truth that I'm hearing.

00:59.096 --> 01:00.498
And by the way, I hear it too.

01:01.058 --> 01:06.165
You might be surprised at that, but very often the sermon I wrote and the sermon that happens are not at all the same.

01:07.006 --> 01:10.090
And sometimes I sit down and I say, that is true.

01:12.593 --> 01:13.435
I wish I'd thought of it.

01:15.457 --> 01:17.860
And when you do that, you need time to process it.

01:17.900 --> 01:19.703
So tonight I'm going to give you some truth.

01:19.843 --> 01:28.374
Out of 1 Peter, we've been going through the book all year, all fall, that we can take and process in God's presence when we go to the table.

01:29.135 --> 01:31.058
Now, we've been going through the book of 1 Peter.

01:31.266 --> 01:35.432
And we're going to read the same passage we read last week, and it's printed in your bulletin.

01:36.693 --> 01:40.558
It's 1 Peter 1 verses 22 to chapter 2 verse 3.

01:41.239 --> 01:42.481
Read along with me if you can.

01:45.184 --> 01:58.482
Now that you have purified yourselves by obeying the truth so that you have sincere love for your brothers, love one another deeply from the heart, for you have been born again

01:58.594 --> 02:02.880
not of perishable seed, but of imperishable through the living and enduring word of God.

02:03.561 --> 02:10.531
For all men are like grass, and all their glory is like the flowers of the field, the grass withers and the flowers fall, but the word of the Lord stands forever.

02:11.192 --> 02:13.074
And this is the word that was preached to you.

02:13.615 --> 02:18.802
Therefore, rid yourselves of all malice and all deceit, hypocrisy, envy, and slander of every kind.

02:19.543 --> 02:27.314
Like newborn babes crave pure spiritual milk so that by it you may grow up into your salvation, now that you have tasted.

02:27.586 --> 02:28.587
that the Lord is good.

02:28.627 --> 02:30.630
This is God's word.

02:30.690 --> 02:34.035
Now we began to look at this passage last week.

02:34.475 --> 02:42.907
This is a sandwich passage because on the one hand, it starts off by saying, having purified yourselves by obeying the truth.

02:43.868 --> 02:48.414
And it ends saying, like newborn babes, grow up into your salvation.

02:49.215 --> 02:53.982
It's actually trying to say what's in the very center, chapter two, verse one and two.

02:54.442 --> 02:57.266
It's an exhortation to love one another.

02:57.858 --> 03:01.943
Peter is writing to Christians, and he's saying, love one another.

03:02.383 --> 03:10.732
But he starts by saying, having purified yourself by obedience to the truth, having been born again, and then he says, love one another.

03:12.154 --> 03:26.770
Because you've been born again, because you're growing, because you're growing in supernatural maturity, because you're having your very insides purified by connecting with the truth and bringing it into your heart, love one another.

03:26.850 --> 03:37.225
In fact, as soon as he says, love one another, read yourselves of all malice and deceit, hypocrisy, envy, and slander of every kind, then he goes back and starts talking again about Christian growth.

03:37.946 --> 03:41.351
He says, like newborn babes crave the pure spiritual milk and so on.

03:41.852 --> 03:43.595
Now, what does he say?

03:45.057 --> 03:47.681
I would like to just take this one point.

03:48.202 --> 03:51.186
There's actually a tremendous amount of material.

03:51.714 --> 03:54.799
that he gives us here about the dynamics for Christian growth.

03:54.919 --> 03:56.201
How do you grow in holiness?

03:56.661 --> 03:58.404
How can you grow in supernatural maturity?

03:58.744 --> 04:04.253
How can you move from where you are right now in a practical way to being more and more like Christ?

04:04.293 --> 04:07.117
How can you have your character honed by him?

04:08.859 --> 04:13.767
Well, it's all here, but tonight I'm just going to show you one part of Christian growth.

04:14.608 --> 04:18.834
One essential sign of Christian growth, one necessary measure of Christian growth.

04:20.194 --> 04:21.836
Love one another deeply.

04:23.578 --> 04:29.144
I'd like to point out two basic principles and then two practical principles that are all here in the text.

04:29.985 --> 04:37.033
Two basic principles about this, love one another deeply, and two practical principles, okay?

04:38.194 --> 04:40.036
First, the two basic principles.

04:40.296 --> 04:45.762
Number one, we learn here that loving other Christians as if they were family.

04:45.782 --> 04:46.483
That's what it's saying.

04:46.503 --> 04:48.946
It says love one another deeply, love from the heart.

04:49.154 --> 04:56.124
You see, it says, you have purified yourselves by the truth so that you have sincere love for your brothers.

04:57.426 --> 05:07.460
Loving other Christians as if they're members of your family is something so hard that he has to surround it with all this other stuff.

05:08.782 --> 05:10.644
You see, he doesn't just say love one another.

05:10.664 --> 05:14.770
He says, you will not be able to do it unless you're born again

05:15.170 --> 05:19.216
And even so, you won't be able to do it unless you're growing rapidly.

05:20.378 --> 05:21.299
Why else would he do this?

05:22.481 --> 05:24.704
Why doesn't he just come right out and say what he's really trying to say?

05:24.744 --> 05:27.088
Read yourselves of all malice and deceit.

05:27.148 --> 05:28.430
You know, love one another deeply.

05:28.710 --> 05:29.411
He can't say it.

05:29.431 --> 05:41.949
He says, because you're purifying yourself, because you're obeying the truth, because you're seeing yourself grow in grace, because you've been born again of the imperishable seed, because you have the supernatural power in you, and because you're growing rapidly.

05:42.210 --> 05:42.811
Love one another.

05:42.831 --> 05:45.074
The first principle is this.

05:45.666 --> 05:52.981
It is an illusion to think that you can just hold up the Christian ethic of love to the world, the Sermon on the Mount, the Golden Rule, turn the other cheek.

05:53.281 --> 05:55.967
Just hold it up and the world will be a better place.

05:56.608 --> 06:07.730
My friends, the Christian ethic of love is something that you are utterly incapable of doing when the Bible says, love one another as brothers and sisters.

06:08.034 --> 06:21.236
When the Bible says, love one another as Christ has loved you, it is asking you for something that's so radical and so deep and so difficult and so far reaching that you not only have to be born again from above to do it, but even that's not enough.

06:21.256 --> 06:25.102
You've got to be growing up into that salvation or there's no way you can do it.

06:26.704 --> 06:30.130
So put it this way, loving other people.

06:30.690 --> 06:40.179
Loving Christians as brothers and sisters is such a deep and total thing and such a difficult thing that you have to be born again by the Spirit and growing rapidly or you're not going to be capable of it.

06:40.199 --> 06:47.406
And it's so silly for therefore for people to think that what preaching is or what the church's job is is just to sort of tell people to love one another.

06:47.446 --> 06:49.728
I've heard this many times.

06:49.748 --> 06:51.389
I've heard it directly and indirectly.

06:51.670 --> 06:57.395
The church's job is not to preach to people and tell them to believe this or that, not to tell people to get converted and so on.

06:57.415 --> 07:00.658
The church's job is just to call the world to love

07:01.026 --> 07:04.871
and to follow the teaching, follow the model in the examples of Jesus Christ.

07:05.852 --> 07:08.315
Now, there's nothing wrong with doing that.

07:09.137 --> 07:13.202
And the more people hear about Jesus' model of relationships, the better.

07:13.522 --> 07:14.884
But don't you see what's going on here?

07:16.526 --> 07:19.850
We are absolutely incapable of loving as Jesus loved us.

07:21.693 --> 07:22.674
Not only

07:23.138 --> 07:31.387
are people who are not born again by imperishable seed incapable of it, but even those of us who are born of imperishable seed aren't capable of it unless we're in a rapid growth pattern.

07:33.128 --> 07:33.909
Let me put it this way.

07:34.930 --> 07:41.457
When people persecute you, when people violate you, when they abuse you, what do you do?

07:41.878 --> 07:45.121
Let me give you three possibilities and pretty much the only three.

07:46.242 --> 07:49.906
One is you can go get them and hate them.

07:50.274 --> 07:51.856
You know, you can seek justice.

07:51.876 --> 07:53.458
You can seek to have the wrong redress.

07:53.478 --> 07:57.043
You know, you go after them and you do it with a vengeful spirit in your heart.

07:57.664 --> 07:59.346
Wanting to see them get their comeuppance.

07:59.647 --> 08:00.708
Wanting to see them fall.

08:01.068 --> 08:02.250
That's the first possibility.

08:02.751 --> 08:06.436
The second possibility is that you don't go after them.

08:06.456 --> 08:08.058
You just sort of, you stuff it.

08:08.919 --> 08:09.660
You clam up.

08:09.700 --> 08:10.361
You don't do it.

08:10.441 --> 08:11.943
You don't go after.

08:11.963 --> 08:12.824
You don't do anything about it.

08:13.064 --> 08:14.667
But you sit and stew and you hate them.

08:16.149 --> 08:20.274
So one view, you know, part, option one, go get them and hate them.

08:20.930 --> 08:23.233
Option two, don't go get him and hate him.

08:24.234 --> 08:27.138
And then there's option three, go get him and love him.

08:28.700 --> 08:37.452
Redress the wrong, go after justice, make sure that justice is done, and do it without one ounce of vengefulness in your heart.

08:38.353 --> 08:45.743
And with nothing but desire to see the persons come to repentance and understand the truth and nothing but love in your heart.

08:46.304 --> 08:49.108
Which of those three do you think is the easiest?

08:49.849 --> 08:50.770
Listen friends,

08:51.138 --> 08:58.894
If you leave anybody to tradition, to common sense, or to their own impulses, they will either, they will always go, number one or number two.

08:59.916 --> 09:03.364
You conflict lovers, go after number one, go get them and hate them.

09:03.644 --> 09:08.354
You conflict haters and avoiders, you stuff it down and you, you know, you don't get them and you hate them.

09:08.374 --> 09:12.082
But the Christian ethic is utterly counterintuitive.

09:12.194 --> 09:15.899
It is utterly the opposite of anything that you would ever even have thought of.

09:16.279 --> 09:18.943
It's against common sense, it's against your impulse, it's against tradition.

09:19.283 --> 09:20.585
People don't believe it's possible.

09:20.925 --> 09:25.371
When people come to me to say, what does the Bible teach I should do when I'm persecuted?

09:25.411 --> 09:26.052
I say it's simple.

09:26.793 --> 09:29.536
You want to not go get him and hate him.

09:29.917 --> 09:31.078
The Bible says reverse that.

09:31.899 --> 09:33.902
You've got to go get him and love him.

09:34.323 --> 09:35.104
And what do people say?

09:35.805 --> 09:36.946
Impossible.

09:37.442 --> 09:38.604
It's ridiculous, they say.

09:38.804 --> 09:40.908
Of course, that's what the Bible says you're supposed to do.

09:41.289 --> 09:42.551
That's what turning the other cheek means.

09:43.392 --> 09:46.157
You see, turning the other cheek does not mean that you let people walk all over you.

09:46.177 --> 09:46.758
Absolutely not.

09:46.838 --> 09:47.479
Call didn't.

09:47.559 --> 09:48.441
He appealed to Caesar.

09:48.521 --> 09:50.384
Jesus did and he protested when he was struck.

09:50.404 --> 09:51.486
Hey, this is illegal, he said.

09:51.546 --> 09:58.418
The Bible always says, you uphold justice for the sake of justice, but you let God be the judge.

09:58.530 --> 10:06.201
You give over the ultimate judgment of that person's character to God, and you go after justice without any vengefulness in your heart.

10:06.221 --> 10:06.702
You forgive.

10:07.102 --> 10:10.026
And somebody says, how in the world can we have to be done?

10:10.126 --> 10:11.088
It's impossible.

10:11.288 --> 10:12.109
That's my first point.

10:12.129 --> 10:13.030
That's the first principle.

10:13.111 --> 10:15.133
The first principle is, it's impossible to do this.

10:17.116 --> 10:18.779
You've not only got to be born again from above.

10:18.819 --> 10:20.241
You've got to be growing like crazy.

10:22.524 --> 10:26.930
The call to love your brothers and sisters, to love one another as Christ has loved you.

10:28.706 --> 10:29.387
It's so hard.

10:30.548 --> 10:35.653
It's so silly to think, all we have to do is hold up the ethic of love, love your neighbor to the world, and it'll become a better place.

10:35.673 --> 10:36.754
You must be born again.

10:36.815 --> 10:39.497
The life of God has got to be running through you like lightning.

10:40.138 --> 10:41.159
You never do it otherwise.

10:41.519 --> 10:48.086
This is probably the reason why in 1 John chapter 2 verse 7 and 8 people have always wondered why John says this.

10:48.106 --> 10:52.551
He says, children, I write no new commandment to you, but an old commandment you had from the beginning.

10:53.412 --> 10:55.314
Again, a new commandment I write to you.

10:55.970 --> 10:58.813
He who's in the light and yet hates his brother is in darkness.

11:00.015 --> 11:03.138
Now, people have always wondered why it is that John says, I'm writing a new commandment to you.

11:03.219 --> 11:04.760
And then he's an old commandment.

11:04.780 --> 11:05.521
It's not a new one.

11:05.541 --> 11:06.562
It's something you've always known.

11:06.603 --> 11:10.347
And then the very next sentence, he says, I'm writing a new commandment to you, love one another.

11:10.888 --> 11:12.570
People have always wondered what he was saying.

11:12.630 --> 11:17.295
And the real answer probably is that in a sense, everybody knows we're supposed to love.

11:17.355 --> 11:23.122
There's every religion, every sacred book in the world says love one another.

11:23.778 --> 11:29.323
And so there's a certain sense in which it's old, but when you become a Christian, real love becomes a new possibility.

11:30.865 --> 11:34.549
There's a real possibility now, but only with supernatural help.

11:34.769 --> 11:37.011
So the first principle is, it's impossible to love.

11:37.692 --> 11:45.199
That's the reason why he has to keep saying, unless you're purifying yourself, unless you're growing, unless you're craving spiritual milk by like newborn babes, they can't do it.

11:45.599 --> 11:48.022
It's the first, second principle.

11:48.042 --> 11:52.466
It almost seems like the reverse, but the second principle is, on the one hand,

11:52.898 --> 12:04.741
This loving spirit is only possible with the new birth and with supernatural growth, but on the other hand, it's absolutely necessary to prove that you really are a Christian.

12:05.463 --> 12:15.442
See, on the one hand, we're saying this spirit of love is only possible with spiritual growth, but on the other hand, it's inevitable with spiritual growth.

12:15.970 --> 12:24.041
As hard as it is, it's inevitable, and therefore, it is maybe the acid test to tell whether or not you really understand the gospel.

12:25.303 --> 12:33.614
In the book of 1 John, which I've already quoted, John tells us that if you want to know you're a Christian, there's three tests.

12:33.755 --> 12:34.916
There's a doctrinal test.

12:36.799 --> 12:39.603
There's a moral test, and there's a social test.

12:39.983 --> 12:42.066
The doctrinal test is you have to believe

12:42.434 --> 12:49.801
that Jesus is the one who he said he was, that he's the son of God and he came and you have to believe in the doctrines of the message of Jesus.

12:50.381 --> 12:55.166
Then secondly, you have to show that you have committed yourself to him by leading a godly life.

12:55.326 --> 13:02.173
But then thirdly, it says, as I already read to you, he that says he's in the light and yet hated his brother is in the darkness.

13:02.613 --> 13:12.242
Now, right here it says in verse 22, now that you have purified yourselves by obeying the truth so that you have sincere love

13:12.354 --> 13:13.736
for your brothers now.

13:14.096 --> 13:15.337
There's a cause effect chain there.

13:16.539 --> 13:21.564
Obaying the truth is now that you purified by obedience unto love.

13:22.125 --> 13:23.066
You see what the chain is?

13:24.427 --> 13:33.577
Obedience and taking the gospel into your heart purifies your soul unto the love of brothers and sisters.

13:33.978 --> 13:38.843
So the point is, here's how you know you've grasped the gospel.

13:38.923 --> 13:41.586
Here's how you know you've purified your heart with a gospel.

13:43.618 --> 13:52.046
You love other Christians without deceit, without hypocrisy, without envy, and without slander of any kind.

13:52.386 --> 13:53.007
That's how you know.

13:54.268 --> 13:55.669
You see, let me put it a couple ways.

13:56.190 --> 13:56.931
It's possible.

13:56.991 --> 14:10.743
The reason love is the acid test of whether or not you really believe the gospel is it's very possible to have both doctrinal purity and moral scrupulosity for other motivations and out of other forces besides the gospel.

14:11.144 --> 14:13.426
It's quite possible.

14:13.570 --> 14:28.631
You see, to be moral out of tradition, out of nostalgia, out of loyalty to your family, out of temperament, out of fastidiousness of conscience, there's all kinds of ways in which you could look at a person who's very moral.

14:30.113 --> 14:33.638
And a person could say, well, that proves that person is a Christian.

14:33.658 --> 14:36.041
That person really understands the message of Christianity.

14:36.081 --> 14:42.610
And what Peter's saying here and what the Bible says is, no, a loving spirit

14:42.882 --> 14:49.508
is a far better acid test of whether you understand the gospel than moral scriptulosity.

14:50.209 --> 14:50.870
Put it another way.

14:51.010 --> 15:09.668
If you are a demanding person, if you are a critical person, if you are a cold person, if you are a distant person, if you're not a very approachable person, you better look hard to see whether or not you've actually purified your soul by taking in the gospel.

15:11.149 --> 15:12.210
It doesn't look good.

15:12.962 --> 15:14.104
This is the acid test.

15:14.764 --> 15:19.992
You see, it's very, very possible to be in deep denial about the gospel.

15:20.112 --> 15:23.396
How do you know that you really believe your sinner saved by grace?

15:24.258 --> 15:24.959
How do you know that?

15:25.920 --> 15:33.330
If you don't believe it, if you believe that you're saved by your performance, if you believe that you're saved by your good deeds,

15:33.890 --> 15:39.397
If you may say theologically on the test, you may say, I know I'm saved by grace, not by works.

15:39.497 --> 15:40.558
I understand all that.

15:41.419 --> 15:42.180
I've gone to redeem her.

15:42.200 --> 15:43.202
I've listened to the sermons.

15:43.582 --> 15:45.344
I know what justification by faith is.

15:46.005 --> 15:55.397
That I'm saved and accepted, not by my works, not by my performance, but only by sheer mercy of God and by what Jesus did on the cross.

15:56.038 --> 15:57.620
Tonight, you may say, I know that.

15:58.000 --> 16:00.003
If I give you a test, you might say, I know that.

16:00.644 --> 16:02.546
And yet you still may be in denial.

16:03.650 --> 16:08.916
You still may actually be a person who believes you're basically saved by your performance and your good works.

16:09.316 --> 16:10.478
Well, how can I know that?

16:10.498 --> 16:11.078
It's simple.

16:11.819 --> 16:16.384
If you are in that position, you will break down into one of two kinds of patterns.

16:16.464 --> 16:24.893
The first one is you will either be smug and self-assured, demanding, cold, imperious, and a critical person.

16:26.235 --> 16:29.138
Wondering why it is that other people can't be as faithful as you.

16:29.698 --> 16:37.547
When you see Christians, the Christian brothers and sisters being stupid, being foolish, doing the wrong thing, hurting you or hurting other people, you absolutely reject them.

16:38.508 --> 16:39.409
You're cold to them.

16:41.852 --> 16:55.287
Or, on the other hand, if you don't believe you're synthesized by grace, instead of being sort of cold and imperious and smug and demanding, you can become defensive and nervous and insecure and easily slighted.

16:56.529 --> 16:57.650
In either case,

16:58.178 --> 17:10.370
You're not relentlessly forgiving, relentlessly warm, relentlessly open, relentlessly approachable, relentlessly gracious, relentlessly vulnerable.

17:11.371 --> 17:13.814
And that's the only way you know you're really a center seat by grace.

17:15.996 --> 17:18.899
Why is there so much pain and suffering in the world?

17:19.340 --> 17:25.746
And how do we handle it in a way that won't destroy us, but could actually make us stronger, wiser, and more hopeful?

17:25.826 --> 17:35.390
All month long on Gospel and Life, Tim Keller is teaching from the book of 1 Peter, and looking at how Peter encouraged early believers who were facing intense suffering in pain.

17:36.132 --> 17:38.738
In his book, Walking with God Through Pain and Suffering,

17:38.786 --> 17:46.633
Dr. Keller takes a deeper look at how, with God's help, we can face life's most intense challenges and confront the hard questions on suffering.

17:47.193 --> 17:53.439
Through deep pastoral insight and real life stories, Dr. Keller explores how we can face pain and suffering in our own lives.

17:53.979 --> 18:03.487
This month, walking with God through pain and suffering is our thank you for your gift to help Gospel and Life share the message of Christ's love and compassion with people all over the world.

18:03.988 --> 18:08.772
So request your copy today at gospelandlife.com.

18:08.752 --> 18:13.578
Now here's Dr. Keller with the remainder of today's teaching.

18:16.621 --> 18:18.103
Don't you see, are you?

18:19.545 --> 18:20.726
Do you find yourself forgiving?

18:21.547 --> 18:24.871
Do you find yourself being positive to people who are criticizing you?

18:26.012 --> 18:29.917
Do you find yourself being able to affirm people even as they're harming you?

18:30.738 --> 18:37.426
Do you find yourself being able to continue to pull for the success of people who have wronged you and harmed you?

18:38.274 --> 18:47.843
Do you find yourself being a gracious, open, and vulnerable in your dealings with people and in your manner and in your face and your tone of voice and in your comments so that people want to come and tell you about their problems?

18:49.485 --> 18:50.286
Or are you pee-vish?

18:50.906 --> 18:51.687
Are you touchy?

18:52.127 --> 18:53.369
Are you sensitive to criticism?

18:53.389 --> 18:55.210
Are you always feeling that people are sliding you?

18:55.531 --> 18:56.071
Are you cold?

18:56.111 --> 18:56.692
Are you smug?

18:56.712 --> 18:57.533
Are you self-righteous?

18:57.593 --> 19:01.356
My friends, this is the way you know that you believe the gospel.

19:02.838 --> 19:07.442
Having purified your soul by obedience to the truth unto

19:08.162 --> 19:17.537
love of other Christians as brothers and sisters, loving them without malice or all deceit, hypocrisy, envy, and slander of any kind.

19:17.958 --> 19:19.460
This is such a searching test.

19:19.801 --> 19:20.842
This is the test.

19:21.604 --> 19:23.206
Oh, I'm not saying doctrine is important.

19:23.226 --> 19:25.650
You can't be a Christian unless you believe in the basic doctrines.

19:25.971 --> 19:33.042
And I'm not saying that morality isn't important because you can't be a Christian unless, as we talked about, we spent three or four weeks on this last month.

19:33.218 --> 19:35.140
Holiness, unless you're living a life of holiness.

19:35.521 --> 19:42.268
But your doctrinal purity and your life of moral fastidiousness and accuracy might have non-gospel roots.

19:44.050 --> 19:45.211
So what is the acid test?

19:47.093 --> 19:47.834
Do you love one another?

19:50.217 --> 19:50.998
You know, here's why.

19:51.038 --> 19:52.740
Take a look at the gospel.

19:52.800 --> 19:53.941
The gospel's got two parts.

19:54.522 --> 19:56.524
It's got the part that says you're a sinner.

19:56.984 --> 19:59.287
And it's got the part that says you're loved and accepted.

19:59.307 --> 20:01.970
Don't you see how that changes?

20:02.306 --> 20:03.508
Do you believe you're a sinner?

20:03.568 --> 20:08.035
Then no matter how mad you get with people, you know you're a sinner.

20:08.075 --> 20:10.078
You know you tend to see things in a selfish way.

20:10.479 --> 20:12.442
You know that you may be wrong.

20:12.462 --> 20:13.524
You know that you're limited.

20:13.544 --> 20:14.646
Your perspective is limited.

20:14.866 --> 20:19.674
You remember what a fool you were five years ago and ten years ago, how many mistakes you made.

20:19.954 --> 20:22.638
You know that's because you're a sinner and you know that figure.

20:22.678 --> 20:25.042
You say, well, if I was a fool ten years ago,

20:25.122 --> 20:29.668
For my vantage point now, I mean that ten years from now, I'll think of myself as a fool now.

20:29.688 --> 20:31.150
I better be careful about what I say.

20:31.170 --> 20:35.416
I better not be so sure about that this person is wrong, that person is wrong.

20:35.436 --> 20:36.317
Do you believe you're a sinner?

20:37.018 --> 20:45.229
Well, you're very careful not to write people off, not to be sure that you can nurse grudges, not to be sure that you're right and the other people are wrong.

20:45.249 --> 20:46.191
Do you believe you're a sinner?

20:46.211 --> 20:51.698
Not only that, you realize, you see, anybody who believes the gospel knows that the difference

20:52.162 --> 20:59.871
between a very respectable person and a street drug pusher is really a small difference.

20:59.891 --> 21:00.952
We've talked about this before.

21:00.972 --> 21:01.733
We're all sinners.

21:03.275 --> 21:04.736
We all fall short of the glory of God.

21:05.097 --> 21:05.817
We're all lost.

21:06.038 --> 21:06.959
Do you believe that?

21:06.979 --> 21:09.662
Then that changes utterly your attitude toward people.

21:10.843 --> 21:12.365
You never can look down on anybody.

21:13.726 --> 21:17.010
You never can be sure that you're always right and the other people are wrong.

21:17.986 --> 21:18.527
Don't you see it?

21:18.547 --> 21:27.415
That's the reason why there's always this forgiveness and there's this sincerity and this openness and this lack of deceit and this lack of slander and gossip and back-biting.

21:27.456 --> 21:28.196
It's got to be there.

21:28.517 --> 21:29.337
Do you believe you're a sinner?

21:29.578 --> 21:30.699
Well, you can't live that way.

21:31.239 --> 21:33.321
But then as the other half of the gospel, do you believe you're loved?

21:33.341 --> 21:34.222
Do you believe you're accepted?

21:34.242 --> 21:35.844
Do you believe you've been forgiven infinitely?

21:35.884 --> 21:39.307
It's obvious.

21:39.848 --> 21:45.874
First on, it says this, to love your Christian sister or brother is a more telling test than orthodoxy.

21:46.178 --> 21:48.021
Though, of course, you must have the truth to be born again.

21:48.121 --> 21:50.284
And it's a more telling test, the mechanical correctness.

21:50.304 --> 21:51.766
Though, of course, you've got to live a holy life.

21:52.627 --> 21:55.512
There are people like the rich young ruler who've always been moral.

21:56.193 --> 21:57.975
All these things I have done since my youth.

21:58.596 --> 22:00.479
But he is a loveless person.

22:02.281 --> 22:04.525
Are you to test?

22:04.625 --> 22:09.672
See, the second principle is you've got to see this kind of spirit of love growing in you.

22:09.712 --> 22:10.994
You've got to see it.

22:12.066 --> 22:15.331
Otherwise, there's no real evidence that you understand the gospel.

22:15.512 --> 22:16.654
You just may be a Pharisee.

22:18.657 --> 22:21.922
Because Pharisees are either very proud or they're very, very inferior.

22:21.962 --> 22:24.607
They either have superiority complexes or inferiority complexes.

22:24.827 --> 22:27.952
They either cold and imperious or they're nervous and defensive.

22:27.972 --> 22:30.416
But in each case, you can't love.

22:31.658 --> 22:36.466
In each case, you can't open, examine yourselves.

22:37.058 --> 22:40.403
Now there's two practical principles we need to apply before we're done.

22:41.064 --> 22:49.798
We said, number one, that this kind of love is absolutely impossible without God's help and a lot of help.

22:50.419 --> 22:51.581
You've got to be in a growth pattern.

22:51.601 --> 22:54.385
And then secondly, we said, this kind of love is absolutely necessary.

22:55.527 --> 23:00.274
It's an outgrowth of believing the gospel and it's absolutely necessary as a test.

23:01.314 --> 23:03.978
Well, right, then somebody says, okay, it's very important that I do it.

23:03.998 --> 23:04.559
How do I do it?

23:04.599 --> 23:10.687
There's actually two guidelines here by which you can judge yourself and also by which you can guide yourself.

23:11.528 --> 23:21.863
And the two tests are, number one, verse 22, now that you have purified yourselves by obeying the truth so that you have sincere love for your brethren, love one another deeply.

23:22.183 --> 23:24.687
Just look at those two words.

23:25.568 --> 23:30.034
Christian love is sincere love and Christian love is deep love.

23:30.658 --> 23:35.243
Let me just tell you what that is, to give you something to think about as you go before the Lord.

23:36.765 --> 23:40.169
Sincere love means, Christian love is always truthful.

23:41.451 --> 23:43.473
Christian love is never just tolerance.

23:44.194 --> 23:49.740
It's a very dangerous move in our society that equates love with tolerance.

23:50.221 --> 23:52.684
So if you love me, you cannot tell me I'm sinning.

23:52.724 --> 23:58.290
If you love me, you cannot make any kind of negative comments about the what I'm doing.

23:58.530 --> 24:00.592
That's not tolerance, but boy, I'll tell you something.

24:00.612 --> 24:07.000
If that's how you define love, that will fly absolutely in the face of not only the Bible, but really common sense.

24:07.520 --> 24:20.275
If you see somebody killing him or herself through some kind of behavior, through the way he or she is working or the way he and she is eating or something like that, for you to say, this is wrong, you're killing yourself, you've got to stop eating like this, you've got to stop living like this.

24:20.615 --> 24:21.436
Is that a lack of love?

24:21.456 --> 24:22.097
Of course not.

24:22.778 --> 24:23.959
Love has got to be sincere.

24:23.999 --> 24:26.482
It's got to be sincere.

24:26.946 --> 24:33.556
There's a tension here, a tremendous tension between truth and love, a tremendous tension, and many times you feel it.

24:34.116 --> 24:39.464
I love this person and I should tell him the truth, but if I tell her the truth, it's gonna hurt her.

24:40.245 --> 24:40.766
What do you do?

24:40.966 --> 24:54.546
Well, just keep this in mind and then move on to deep love, but for a moment, sincere love, not just sincere, but sincere love, not just love, but sincere love, means on the one hand,

24:54.850 --> 24:56.151
We better not be cowards.

24:56.592 --> 25:03.359
Oh, how many times have you chickened out and not said something truthful to somebody you love?

25:03.379 --> 25:04.620
And you know what you always tell yourself?

25:05.681 --> 25:08.284
You know where your coward is lies in a certain kind of deception.

25:08.304 --> 25:10.866
You say, I couldn't do that because it would hurt her so much.

25:12.127 --> 25:12.768
Give me a break.

25:13.068 --> 25:14.910
You can't do it because it'll hurt you so much.

25:16.412 --> 25:22.578
You have to realize that it's terribly selfish in many cases for you to not tell somebody the truth.

25:23.074 --> 25:25.076
Because you're saying, well, it hurt her so much.

25:25.116 --> 25:27.198
What you mean is you're not going to be able to handle.

25:27.299 --> 25:29.381
You don't want to have her complaining.

25:29.441 --> 25:32.224
You don't want to have her saying that you're being judgmental.

25:32.304 --> 25:34.326
You're thinking of you.

25:34.346 --> 25:35.087
You're not thinking of her.

25:35.127 --> 25:38.531
You're thinking of you being a coward.

25:39.392 --> 25:40.373
We can't take the flak.

25:40.773 --> 25:44.798
We can't take the guilt that will come from the person saying, why did you say this?

25:45.619 --> 25:51.405
Very often, when we unmask our cowardice as a form of selfishness, not kindness and not love, it helps.

25:51.445 --> 25:52.466
But on the other hand,

25:53.954 --> 25:56.977
I said, it's not sincere, it's love, it's not just love, it's sincere love.

25:57.918 --> 26:05.026
On the other hand, the motivation for telling people the truth is always their need.

26:05.547 --> 26:06.488
They need the truth.

26:06.528 --> 26:20.484
And therefore, if you tell somebody the truth and you don't tell them in a way, you don't tell them at a time, you don't tell them in a context, you don't tell them in a form that they can hear, you just tell them, well, I told them the truth.

26:21.124 --> 26:22.706
That's not sincere love.

26:23.106 --> 26:24.027
That's just sincere.

26:24.087 --> 26:25.990
That's not what we're talking about.

26:26.811 --> 26:28.593
You see, on the one hand, watch out.

26:28.633 --> 26:29.554
Are you a coward?

26:30.135 --> 26:31.857
Is that the reason why your love isn't sincere?

26:32.257 --> 26:41.869
Are there people who you should be loving by telling the truth and you're not doing it and you're justifying it by saying, ah, well, that'll hurt the person when actually what you're really saying is it'll hurt me.

26:42.390 --> 26:48.817
But on the other hand, are you willing to make sure that the person hears the truth in the right way?

26:49.058 --> 26:52.562
You know, when you watch a kitchen floor,

26:53.122 --> 27:00.772
One way you'll see all the dirt on the floor, one way to deal with the dirt is just that you pick up the bucket with all the soap in it and the water and just throw it on the floor.

27:00.792 --> 27:01.113
That's the way.

27:01.153 --> 27:05.739
The whole bucket, that'll move the dirt around and then it'll make quite a mess.

27:05.759 --> 27:12.408
It'll move the dirt around but in the end it'll be even worse because the dirt will be kind of washed over in the corner and so on.

27:12.809 --> 27:19.698
The way to get the floor clean is to bring the water out onto the floor in stages then bring it back in and

27:19.778 --> 27:22.162
you know, rinse it out, and then bring it back in.

27:22.182 --> 27:26.789
And eventually you might use the entire bucket, and that's the way to deal with the dirt.

27:27.450 --> 27:36.603
That's how you're supposed to tell people the truth in a way, in a form, in a context, at a time, that they can hear it, because you tell them the truth out of love, because they need it.

27:37.565 --> 27:40.449
And you don't tell them the truth in a way that they don't even get it.

27:41.411 --> 27:42.272
Sincere love.

27:42.933 --> 27:46.118
Have you got a love that's sincere in your relationships?

27:46.839 --> 27:48.882
But then secondly, deep love.

27:49.666 --> 27:59.617
This word deep, it says, now that you've purified yourself by obeying the truth so that you have sincere love for your brother and love one another deeply from the heart, love one another deeply.

27:59.977 --> 28:02.480
This word deep is an awfully interesting Greek word.

28:03.561 --> 28:08.046
The more I study that I realize what it really means is to be stretched to the limit.

28:08.947 --> 28:11.209
It's actually a distance running word.

28:11.770 --> 28:15.794
It's used to describe Jesus in the garden.

28:17.090 --> 28:19.474
you know, just about at the end of his tether.

28:19.874 --> 28:24.541
And the word to love one of the deeply really means to love one another strenuously.

28:25.863 --> 28:26.664
And what does that mean?

28:27.766 --> 28:28.848
It's very much like running.

28:29.809 --> 28:38.482
One of the weird things about physical exercise is that the more you do it, in general, the more strength you feel.

28:39.223 --> 28:42.528
But in the short run, you feel like you want to die.

28:42.588 --> 28:44.091
I mean, that's what exercise is all about.

28:44.371 --> 28:46.354
It's so odd that the very thing

28:47.010 --> 28:55.541
that gives you overall more energy and more strength and more power in the long run, in the short run, drains you.

28:56.962 --> 28:57.843
Same thing with love.

28:58.144 --> 28:59.305
You know what the ironic thing is?

28:59.365 --> 29:06.614
If you don't exercise, you actually, if you don't drain yourself through exercise, the lack of exercise will drain you.

29:07.776 --> 29:16.146
If you've ever been in bed recuperating from a sickness, you had to be in bed for an entire week, because that ever happened and you get up and you haven't even been moving around and you can't believe how weak you are.

29:16.866 --> 29:17.787
You're so ironic.

29:18.889 --> 29:24.076
Only by draining yourself through exercise are you not drained during the rest of your life.

29:24.316 --> 29:26.680
And if you don't drain yourself through exercise, you are drained.

29:26.700 --> 29:27.541
It's very odd.

29:27.561 --> 29:28.402
Love is the same way.

29:29.664 --> 29:30.545
Love is strenuous.

29:31.126 --> 29:32.848
Christian love doesn't give up on people.

29:33.709 --> 29:34.871
It's very much like running a race.

29:34.891 --> 29:35.852
You stick with it.

29:35.872 --> 29:37.394
You want to give up one more lap.

29:38.336 --> 29:39.477
You don't give up on people.

29:40.539 --> 29:42.581
Paul says love never gives up.

29:43.122 --> 29:45.906
There's a difference between the way Christians relate to each other.

29:46.146 --> 29:47.849
Are there Christians that you've given up on?

29:47.929 --> 29:48.409
Oh, look.

29:48.429 --> 29:48.790
Oh, look.

29:49.391 --> 29:49.751
I know.

29:49.811 --> 29:53.236
At a certain point, you're telling somebody the truth and they won't hear it.

29:53.297 --> 29:55.079
Then you have to back off, in that sense.

29:55.740 --> 29:56.541
I understand that.

29:57.162 --> 30:01.228
Sometimes people are draining you and you've got to conserve yourself just like a forest.

30:01.288 --> 30:02.991
You know, you can't just cut all the trees down.

30:03.271 --> 30:04.493
You've got to cut enough trees down.

30:04.513 --> 30:07.858
You've got to plant enough trees so the forest continues to give out wood.

30:08.290 --> 30:11.613
In the same way, you can't just let somebody cut your entire forest down.

30:11.653 --> 30:14.696
You can't let somebody drain you to the ground, so you've got nothing for that person or anybody else.

30:15.037 --> 30:17.479
So there's times in which you have to pull back absolutely.

30:17.760 --> 30:20.763
But in the long run, you do not give up on, but you don't write anybody off.

30:20.783 --> 30:23.505
You don't say to another Christian brother or sister, forget you.

30:25.728 --> 30:27.049
You have to love strenuously.

30:27.069 --> 30:28.050
You have to stick with it.

30:28.070 --> 30:29.712
You have to keep up on the race.

30:30.993 --> 30:31.653
Strenuous.

30:32.214 --> 30:36.178
Or another aspect, of course, is it says, you're supposed to put away all malice.

30:36.450 --> 30:37.852
And slander, you know what that means?

30:37.892 --> 30:38.894
You have to forgive.

30:39.655 --> 30:41.398
There's nothing more strenuous than forgiving.

30:43.441 --> 30:49.871
If somebody, if I give you my radio and you break it and I say, I forgive you, what have I done?

30:50.412 --> 30:51.373
I absorb the cost.

30:52.074 --> 30:53.296
I don't make you pay, I pay.

30:54.358 --> 30:58.244
And if somebody wrongs you and you say, I forgive, you know what that means?

30:58.805 --> 31:00.708
You can either exact the price out of that person.

31:01.749 --> 31:02.891
You can be cold of that person.

31:03.432 --> 31:04.914
You can avoid that person.

31:05.122 --> 31:07.445
You know when she's coming down this aisle, you go back out that aisle?

31:10.049 --> 31:13.854
You can root for that person to lose, to fail, to get comeuppance.

31:15.256 --> 31:18.460
You can stick little pins in the person in your own heart.

31:19.041 --> 31:20.343
That's exacting the price.

31:21.064 --> 31:22.546
That's making her pay for the radio.

31:23.046 --> 31:24.849
Or you can say, I forgive you.

31:25.289 --> 31:26.912
Which means you absorb the cost.

31:27.693 --> 31:28.954
You pull for that person.

31:29.195 --> 31:30.577
You're cordial to that person.

31:31.618 --> 31:34.642
You refuse to replay the tapes of what she did to you.

31:34.850 --> 31:35.451
in your heart.

31:36.353 --> 31:37.414
That's strenuous.

31:37.595 --> 31:38.556
You absorb the cost.

31:38.596 --> 31:39.478
That's strenuous.

31:40.980 --> 31:44.105
And I tell you something, there's people here saying, that's too hard for me.

31:44.526 --> 31:45.708
Well, it's just like exercise.

31:46.209 --> 32:01.234
If you don't exercise, if you will lay in bed, because you say, oh, it's too much effort, the less you do, the less you'll be able to do, the less you exercise, the less you'll be able to exercise, the less you love, the less you'll be able to love, the more you go all the way, the more you

32:01.474 --> 32:09.743
keep with people, and you stick with people, and you love people, and you forgive people, and the more strenuous you are in your love, the more power you're gonna have in your life.

32:11.305 --> 32:12.146
Is your love sincere?

32:12.206 --> 32:14.989
Is your love deep?

32:15.009 --> 32:16.911
Are you a kind of truth-telling person?

32:17.432 --> 32:19.294
You know, there's sincerity, there's no depth.

32:20.115 --> 32:23.118
Or are you a very feeling person, but there's no truth?

32:24.600 --> 32:25.661
We're going to the Lord's table.

32:27.363 --> 32:30.226
Jesus says, if you've got something against your brother's sister, leave,

32:32.578 --> 32:35.002
leave your gift at the altar and make it right.

32:36.083 --> 33:01.682
What I think that's gotta mean is if you know you've given up on people, if you know you're not loving your Christian brother's sister deeply, if you know you're not loving them strenuously, you're not forgiving, you're giving up on them, you're avoiding them, look at the gospel and you'll be able to forgive, purify your soul through taking then the truth and you'll be able to do it tonight and don't take the cup

33:01.826 --> 33:03.888
and take the bread unless you're willing to do that.

33:05.170 --> 33:11.037
Mark chapter 11, I think it says, if you stand praying and you find that you have anything against anyone, forgive me.

33:12.699 --> 33:15.302
It's strenuous, but the power will come.

33:16.724 --> 33:19.507
The more you do it, the more you can do it.

33:20.228 --> 33:20.689
Let's pray.

33:21.810 --> 33:28.498
Father, we pray that at Redeemer, we will be characterized by both sincere and deep love.

33:28.898 --> 33:41.242
and we pray that you help us to make strides toward that tonight as you purify us unto the love of our brothers and sisters as we take your truth in and as we meet you over the table, we pray this in Jesus name.

33:47.134 --> 33:47.234
Amen.

33:47.254 --> 33:49.138
Thanks for listening to today's teaching.

33:49.378 --> 33:55.346
It's our prayer that you were encouraged by it and that it helps you apply the gospel to your life and share it with others.

33:55.806 --> 33:59.571
For more helpful resources from Tim Keller, visit gospelandlife.com.

